{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> φροντ-ίζω</b>, <br /> <i>future</i> <i>Attic dialect</i> ιῶ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 1234, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 125, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 2.1.24, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἐφρόντισα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 245 (troch.)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], etc.: <i>perfect</i> πεφρόντικα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 773, 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 352, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 263, etc.:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>middle</i>, <i>future</i> φροντιοῦμαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 343 (assuming variant)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:— <i>passive</i>, see infr. IV: (φροντίς): <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>consider, reflect, take thought,</b> φροντίζων εὑρίσκω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.24, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 1034, “Supp.” 418 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 75, +others; ζητεῖν καὶ φ. καὶ βουλεύεσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 9.41 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>give heed, pay attention,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 558a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> <b>to be thoughtful</b> or <b>anxious,</b> πεφροντικὸς βλέπεις you look <b>careworn,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 773; τίς δ᾽ ἔστιν ὁ.. φροντίζω; 2nd c.AD: Phrynichus Atticista \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] Comedy texts 21; τὸ πεφροντικός, as <i>substantive</i>, <b>care, thought,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.983b. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> with an object, <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> <i>of things</i>, <b>consider, ponder,</b> ἔχθος ἐμόν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 1247; Σωκράτης.. -ίζων τι ἕστηκε 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 220c; δεινά.. τοῖς τεκοῦσι φροντίσαι 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 245 (troch.)\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; [ὀνείρατα] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.16 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>].; <b>devise,</b> μηχανήν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 5.67; τοῦτο φ. ὅκως μὴ λείψομαι [prev. author] 7.8.ά\">Refs</a>] (nisi to be read τοῦτον); ἐκεῖνο δ᾽ οὐ πεφροντίκαμεν, ὅτῳ τρόπῳ.. μνημονεύσομεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 263 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also directly followed by a <i>relative</i> clause, φ. ἥντιν᾽ [ὁδὸν] ἴω προτέρην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 912; φ. πρὸς ἑωυτὸν ὡς δώσει 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.100; ἐφρόντισ᾽ ᾗ διέφθαρται βίος 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 376; φ. ὅ τι βούλεται ἑαυτὸν καλεῖν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 39.2, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.7.6 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; φ. τί ποτε τοῦτ᾽ ἔστι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Cyr.” 3.3.32 \">Refs</a>]; <b>take thought</b> that.., <b>see to it</b> that, ὅπως.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 29e, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.6.8, “PHib.” 1.82.10 (3rd c.BC); later ἵνα.. [prev. work] 43.7 (3rd c.BC), 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 2.8.8 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὡς.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PTeb.” 10.6, +others (2nd c.BC)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Tit.3.8, “BGU” 8 ii 4 (3rd c.AD), etc.: followed by μή\">NT+3rd c.AD+</a>] with <i>subjunctive</i>, φ. μὴ ἄριστον ᾖ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.155, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 4.2.39, compare below 111 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐδὲν φ. εἰ.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 503a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; φ. εἴτε.., εἴτε.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “R.” 344e \">Refs</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Fabius Maximus” 12 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: with <i>participle</i>, φροντίζεθ᾽ ὡς μαχούμενοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1370. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> with <i>genitive</i>, <b>take thought for, give heed to</b> a thing, <b>regard</b> it, mostly with a <i>negative</i> expressed or implied, σοὶ δ᾽ ἔμεθεν μὲν ἀπήχθετο φροντίσδην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Sappho Lyrica 41 (assuming variant); Περσέων οὐδὲν φ. 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.97, compare 100, 151, 4.167; γῆ αὐχμοῦ φροντίζουσα οὐδέν [prev. author] 4.198; Πενθέως οὐ φροντίσας 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 637 (troch.); μηδὲν ὅρκου φροντίσῃς 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 915; τῶν οἰκετῶν.. μηδὲν φ. 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 7.17 \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; μησενὸς ἄλλου φ., πλὴν ὅπως.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 15.305; οὐδὲ τῶν νόμων φροντίζουσι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 563d; τὸ παράπαν θεῶν μὴ φ. [prev. author] “Lg.” 701c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; conversely, τοὺς θεοὺς φ. οὐδὲν τῶν ἀνθρωπίνων[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 888c, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Ἐπιτρέποντες” 552 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: so with <i>adverbs</i> implying a <i>negative</i>, σμικρὰ φ. ὄχλου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 801 (troch.); ὀλίγον φ. δεσποτῶν [prev. author] “Cyc.” 163; σμικρὸν φ. Σωκράτους 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 91c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also without <i>negative</i>, οὗπερ δεῖ μάλιστα φ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 242; τοῦ μὲν ὀνόματος φ., τοῦ δὲ πράγματος ἀμελεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.27; σφόδρα σοῦ φ. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.11.10; εἰ σοφὸς ἀνὴρ ταφῆς φροντιεῖ 2nd c.BC: Demetrius Lacon Philosophus “Herc.” 1012.26 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; later, <b>to be steward</b> or <b>bailiff,</b> τῶν ὑπαρχόντων τινός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “BGU” 300.4 (2nd c.AD): so with Preps., φ. περί τινος\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] <b>to be concerned</b> or <b>anxious</b> about, σφέων αὐτῶν πέρι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.36, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 1.1.12, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 709; ὑπέρ τινος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthyphro” 4d; ὑπὲρ σωτηρίας 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 1.2; less frequently in this sense with _accusative_ only, [Σωκράτης] τἄλλα μὲν πεφρόντικεν 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 352; ἄλλο οὐδὲν φροντίζειν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 501e; ἀλλ᾽ οὐ τὰ βίου.. δεῖ φροντίσαι 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 330; ἡ δ᾽ ἐφρόντισ᾽ οὐδὲ ἕν 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 302 (troch.). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.2.b</b></Level4> later, <b>see to, provide for, furnish,</b> σιτάριον, χρήσιμα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “ZUP” 73.5, 69.2 (both 2nd c.BC)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; τὰ ἐπιβάλλοντα τῇ ἑορτῇ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “BGU” 845.18 (2nd c.AD)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; μηδὲν φροντίσας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 80. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.2.c</b></Level4> with <i>accusative</i> et <i>participle</i>, οὐ φροντίζει σκληρῶς σε καθήμενον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 783 (_anapaest meter_). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> the object is frequently unexpressed, ἐφρόντιζε ἱστορέων, i. e. inquired carefully, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.56 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οἲ τοὺς φίλους βλάπτοντες οὐ φροντίζετε who though ye do mischief to your friends <b>reck</b> not <b>of</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 256 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μὴ φροντίσῃς <b>heed</b> it not [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 228; οὐ, μὰ Δἴ, οὐδ᾽ ἐφρόντισα [prev. author] “Ra.” 493, compare 650, “Pl.” 215, 704 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; with <i>participle</i>, τοιαῦτα.. γιγνόμενα.. ὁρῶντες οὐδὲν φροντίζετε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.23. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>middle</i> in <i>signification</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 11.1, φροντιζόμενον μή.. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Hiero” 7.10: with _accusative_, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 343 (assuming variant). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> later in <i>passive</i>, <b>to be an object of thought</b> or <b>care,</b> πεφροντισμένος <b>carefully thought out;</b> λόγος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 15.78, 16.32; λόγοι πεφρ. εὖ 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Vitae Sophistarum” 1.11; τρέφονται τροφῇ πεφροντισμένῃ 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “De Natura Animalium - Ar.Byzantine Epit.” 7.9 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; of a ward, ἡ-ομένη ὑπ᾽ ἐμοῦ θυγατριδῆ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “BGU” 300.16 (2nd c.AD). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5431","accentedUnicode":"φροντίζω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5424","matchingForm":"φρήν","stepTransliteration":"frēn","gloss":"thinking","_zh_tw_Gloss":"心志上","_es_Gloss":"modo de pensar","_zh_Gloss":"心志上"}],"shortDef":"to be careful, concerned","mediumDef":"to be careful, concerned <br /><b>to be considerate, concerned, be careful,</b> <ref='Tit.3.8'>Tit. 3:8</ref>*","stepGloss":"be careful","stepTransliteration":"frontizō","count":1,"_es_Definition":"concentrarse en, estar preocupado por (hacer algo), empeñarse en","_zh_tw_Definition":"思考, 留心 (多 3:8)","_zh_Definition":"思考, 留心 (多 3:8)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"áp dụng.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"留心","_es_Gloss":"tener cuidado","_zh_Gloss":"留心"}]}